{"cursor":"19744","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Steven Heller image = Steven Heller.jpg caption = Steven Heller\n| birth_date = birth_place = New York City\n}}\n\n'Steven Heller' (born 1950) is an American art director, journalist, critic,\nauthor, and editor who specializes on topics related to graphic design.\n\nSteven Heller is author and co-author of many works on the history of\nillustration, typography, and many subjects related to graphic design. He has\npublished more than eighty titles and written articles for magazines including\nAffiche, [[Baseline (magazine)|Baseline]], Creation, Design, Design Issues,\n[[Design Observer]], [[Eye magazine|Eye]], Graphis, How, I.D., Oxymoron,\n[[Mother Jones (magazine)|Mother Jones]], [[The New York Times Book Review]],\n[[Print (magazine)|Print]], Speak, and U&lc.\n\nFor thirty-three years Heller was a senior art director of [[U&lc magazine]], a\npublication devoted to typography. As of 2007, he is co-chair with Lita Talarico\nof the MFA Designer as Author program at the School of Visual Arts in New York\nCity (D-\nCrit). [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9C03E5DF1F3FF93AA257-\n52C1A9609C8B63 \"Up Front\"], [[The New York Times]], November 16, 2007. Accessed\nNovember 27, 2007. He has collaborated on books with graphic designer,\nLouise Fili, who is his wife, as well as with others including the Design\nDialogue series.\n","linknr":233,"url":"Steven_Heller_(graphic_design)","recorded":1375069995,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Steven_Heller_(design_writer)&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Steven_Heller_(design_writer)&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Steven_Heller_(design_writer)","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.